<item>
            <title>[COMPRESS-463] ZipArchiveInputStream should throw if stored entry ends prematurely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/COMPRESS-463</link>
                <project id="12310904" key="COMPRESS">Commons Compress</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the archive stream ends before the claimed size of a stored entry has been hit the stream returns -1 rather than throwing a &quot;truncated archive&quot; exception like it would do for deflated entries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because of this it is impossible to detect a truncated stored entry.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13178094">COMPRESS-463</key>
            <summary>ZipArchiveInputStream should throw if stored entry ends prematurely</summary>
