                            <comment id="17163559" author="red_devil99" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2020 13:15:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bodewig&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bodewig&quot;&gt;bodewig&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Hi, I reached out to this Bug Id, can you please provide more details regarding the versions before 1.17?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I saw your email thread here:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/b8da751fc0ca949534cdf2744111da6bb0349d2798fac94b0a50f330@%3Cannounce.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/b8da751fc0ca949534cdf2744111da6bb0349d2798fac94b0a50f330@%3Cannounce.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do the version before 1.7 are affected as well?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks in advance!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17163635" author="bodewig" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2020 14:33:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With Compress 1.7 the implementation for reading stored entries has changed and introduced a flaky behavior where &lt;tt&gt;read&lt;/tt&gt; would alternate between -1 and a non-negative number returned which can throw&#160;&lt;tt&gt;InputStreamReader&lt;/tt&gt; into an infinite loop. Compress 1.6 and earlier would have returned -1 consistently and thus not cause an infinite loop - but it would also not properly signal the archive as corrupted and give you the false impression you&apos;d have read the entry completely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
